Subject: Re: [T2] 72 to 77 fuel tank stuff

On 4/17/05 8:38 PM, "Chris" <cflesher1(-at-)yahoo.com> wrote:

> 1) there were 4 screws from the bottom on the firewall on my 72.  Isn't this
> uncommon?  I thought there were only 2.  Which years had 4 and which 2?  My 73
> had 2 so my guess is that 2 started in 73.

I've seen 4 holes on 72 as well (but only two screws).
 
> 2) My 72 tank has the vent tube on top in middle (in addition to the 2 small
> ones that go to canister) that goes to filler neck.

> I'm putting a 77 F.I. tank in that has no such vent.  I do recall that my 73
> had no such vent either (another thing starting in 73?) and was always very
> difficult to fill with gas.  Do the two small vents (for canister) replace the
> large vent in middle for the purpose of breathing during filling up?  Without
> this middle tank vent and the newly open filler neck line, OK to tap the
> filler neck line into the vent lines (to canister) to restore its function?

The middle vent is only a breather for the filler tube. The other two pipes
serve the same purpose at the later fuel tank: breathers for the charcoal
canister to accept the fumes.
  
> 3)  With the installation of the 77 F.I. tank, will the newer style guage
> sender work with 72 guage or will I have to get a 77 style guage?

People have been able to fit the newer sender into the old tanks so I
suspect it might work.

